## Emergency Notification Generator

Build a single-page Incident Report form replicating the described table layout, with PNG export and mailto sending.

### Route
- Replace `src/routes/index.tsx` placeholder with the Incident Report page (title + meta updated).

### Component
New `src/components/IncidentReport.tsx` containing:
- Controlled state object for all fields (status, severity, priority, app, description, leader, team, otherTeams, nextComm, ticketNumber, pir).
- Rigid HTML `<table>` layout wrapped in a ref'd container for capture.
- Left-column header cells: `bg-[#188665] text-white font-bold`.
- All cell borders: `border border-[#188665]` (solid).
- shadcn `Select`, `Input`, `Textarea` with `border-0 shadow-none focus-visible:ring-0 rounded-none h-full w-full bg-transparent` so they blend into cells.
- Per-field background/text overrides:
  - Status select: white bg, light green text.
  - Severity + Priority selects: red bg (`bg-red-500`), black text.
  - Aplikacja/Usługa select: white bg, dark blue bold text.
- Textarea for "Opis incydentu" — multi-line, monospace optional, supports bullets/timestamps as plain text.

### Rows (in order)
1. Status Awarii — header cell + 3 selects in one row (Status / Severity / Priority).
2. Aplikacja/Usługa — select (OMR/xRDJ/IKS, etc.).
3. Opis incydentu\Aktualny stan — large textarea.
4. IT Tribe Leader — text input.
5. Zespół zaangażowany — text input.
6. Inne zespoły zaangażowane — text input.
7. Następna komunikacja — text input (with datalist of common values).
8. Numer incydentu w Service Now — text input.
9. PIR [Y/N] — select (TAK/NIE).

### Actions (buttons below table)
- **Export to PNG**: install `html2canvas`; capture table ref; trigger download `incident-report-<timestamp>.png`.
- **Send via Email**: build plain-text body listing each label + value on separate lines; build subject `Incident Report: <app> - <status>`; `window.location.href = mailto:?subject=...&body=...` with proper `encodeURIComponent`.

### Dependencies
- `bun add html2canvas`
- Reuse existing shadcn `select`, `input`, `textarea`, `button`.

### Notes
- Polish labels exactly as provided.
- Default select option labels visible when empty (placeholder).
- Responsive: table stays fixed-width on desktop, horizontally scrollable on mobile.
